7","1024–Female":"1024–Overleden","1084–1147":"1084–1147","1035–1071":"1035–1071","1030–1102":"1030–1102","about 1071":"circa 1071","about 1084":"circa 1084","1147":"1147","1102":"1102","1035":"1035","1024":"1024","about 1147":"circa 1147","about 1102":"circa 1102","1030":"1030","1084":"1084","1060":"1060","1071":"1071","Crecy, Ardennes, Champagne-Ardenne, France":"Crécy, Ardennes, Champagne-Ardenne, Frankrijk","Europe":"Europa","Vincennes, Val-de-Marne, Île-de-France, France":"Vincennes, Val-de-Marne, Île-de-France, Frankrijk","Champagne, France":"Champagne, Frankrijk"},"en":{"1060–1147":"1060–1147","1024–Female":"1024–Deceased","1084–1147":"1084–1147","1035–1071":"1035–1071","1030–1102":"1030–1102","about 1071":"about 1071","about 1084":"about 1084","1147":"1147","1102":"1102","1035":"1035","1024":"1024","about 1147":"about 1147","about 1102":"about 1102","1030":"1030","1084":"1084","1060":"1060","1071":"1071","Crecy, Ardennes, Champagne-Ardenne, France":"Crécy, Ardennes, Champagne-Ardenne, France","Europe":"Europe","Vincennes, Val-de-Marne, Île-de-France, France":"Vincennes, Val-de-Marne, Île-de-France, France","Champagne, France":"Champagne, France","nameMeanings":[{"name":"de","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Dilip, Anirban, Gopal, Alok, Anindya, Arunava, Asit, Asok, Dibyendu, Goutam, Indra, Indranil.","Indian: variant of   Dey  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Dey","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Ashit, Indu, Naina, Partha, Soumya, Ajit, Anjan, Anjana, Anup, Arjun, Arun, Ashim.","English, Scottish, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"Crecy","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of Family Names in Britain and Ireland © University of the West of England 2016","meanings":["Norman, English:  see  Creasey  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Creasey","meanings":["English (Lincolnshire, or Norman origin): habitational name from Cressy in Seine-Maritime, France (see   Cressy  ).","Possibly an Americanized form of any of the German names mentioned at   Creasy  ."]}]},{"name":"Guy","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From an Old French name, of Germanic (Frankish) origin, originally a short form of a compound name starting with <i>witu</i> ‘wood’ or <i>wīt</i> ‘wide’. This was adopted by the Normans and introduced by them to England. In Old French initial <i>w-</i> regularly became <i>gu-</i>. The usual Norman forms of the name were <i>Gy</i> or <i>Guido</i>. In medieval Latin the same name is found as <i>Wido</i>. It was a popular name among the Normans, enhanced no doubt by the romance of Guy of Warwick, recounting the exploits of a folk hero of the Crusades."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Guy de Crecy sur serre de Corbeil was born in 1060, in Europe, his father, Renaud de Crecy, was 26 and his mother, Eustachie de Dammartin, was 30. He married Isabelle de Crecy de Corbeil. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter. He died in 1147, at the age of 87."},"et":{"1060–1147":"1060–1147","1024–Female":"1024–Surnud","1084–1147":"1084–1147","1035–1071":"1035–1071","1030–1102":"1030–1102","about 1071":"umbes 1071","about 1084":"umbes 1084","1147":"1147","1102":"1102","1035":"1035","1024":"1024","about 1147":"umbes 1147","about 1102":"umbes 1102","1030":"1030","1084":"1084","1060":"1060","1071":"1071","Crecy, Ardennes, Champagne-Ardenne, France":"Crécy, Ardennes, Champagne-Ardenne, Prantsusmaa","Europe":"Europe","Vincennes, Val-de-Marne, Île-de-France, France":"Vincennes, Val-de-Marne, Île-de-France, Prantsusmaa","Champagne, France":"Champagne, Prantsusmaa"},"fi":{"1060–1147":"1060–1147","1024–Female":"1024–Kuollut","1084–1147":"1084–